    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\nAdd `reorder_batch` to `AttentionMetadataBuilder`. As `AttentionGroup.metadata_builder` is `AttentionMetadataBuilder`  type. \nhttps://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/c8851a47235f5dfd3da3abf6c89453b3bdb41ad1/vllm/v1/worker/utils.py#L129-L133\n\nCode in cpu_model_runner `_may_reorder_batch` will just use assert to check the `metadata_builder` is a subclass `TorchSDPAMetadataBuilderV1` of `AttentionMetadataBuilder`. `AttentionMetadataBuilder` has no method called `reorder_batch` and only `TorchSDPAMetadataBuilderV1` has one. Python static code checker will complain that `metadata_builder` does not have a method called `reorder_batch`.\nhttps://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/c8851a47235f5dfd3da3abf6c89453b3bdb41ad1/vllm/v1/worker/cpu_model_runner.py#L58-L62\n\nThis PR adds `reorder_batch` to the base class definition.\n## Test Plan\nNA\n## Test Result\nNA\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
